-- Women Manage 8% of German Farms as Agriculture Keeps Male Bias
-- B y   R u d y   R u i t e n b e r g
-- 2012-01-17T12:20:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/women-manage-8-of-german-farms-as-agriculture-keeps-male-bias.html
Women were in charge of 8 percent of
 Germany ’s 299,000 farms in 2010, the government statistics
office reported.  “Men traditionally dominate management positions in
agriculture,” Wiesbaden, Germany-based Statistisches Bundesamt
Deutschland wrote in a  report  on its website today.  Sixty-four percent of about 25,000 female farm
managers in Germany ran their agricultural holding on a part-
time basis, compared with 48 percent of men, according to the
statistics office.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rudy Ruitenberg in Paris at 
 rruitenberg@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
